text.section:
In its order, the court shall:
Find that no legal cause for forfeiture exists, and dismiss the petition;
Direct the corporation to remedy one or more grievances, on penalty of forfeiture of the charter if they are not remedied within the time set by the order; or
Find that legal cause for forfeiture has been shown and that the public interest requires a forfeiture;
Declare the charter forfeited and the corporation dissolved; and
Appoint a receiver of the assets of the corporation.
